every user-facing string in the source (AST-harvested — all arguments to the
Printer methods + errors.New/fmt.Errorf/fmt.Sprintf, plus the text/remedy
fields of healthLine{} and doctor.Result{} literals, both "…" and `…` raw
strings). The completeness backstop: catches the failure remedies and the
multi-step flows (ingest steps, login, progress, confirmations) not shown as a
screen. %s/%d are runtime placeholders.

